Tom Brady now has another Pro Bowler to throw to. The Buccaneers are signing Julio Jones to a one-year contract, according to multiple reports. Jones, 33, was a free agent after being released by the Titans in March. Jones, a seven-time Pro Bowler, spent one season with Tennessee after 10 years with the Falcons. He had a disappointing 2021 season, making 31 receptions for 434 yards with one touchdown in 10 games. Tampa Bayâ€™s signing of Jones comes on the heels of the team adding former Giants tight end Kyle Rudolph. The Buccaneers now boast a receiver trio of Jones, Mike Evans and Chris Godwin. It is unclear, however, when Godwin will be ready to return after tearing his ACL at the end of last season.